arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon beat Notts County to tee up Walsall showdown in League Two play-off final
arts.sum: Josh Neufville’s early goal sets seal on semi-final victory as Dons target return to third tier at Wembley

arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon defeat Notts County to reach League Two play-off final at Wembley
arts.sum: AFC Wimbledon secured their place in the League Two play-off final with a 1-0 win over Notts County at Plough Lane today, completing a 2-0 aggregate victory. Neufville beat his marker and sent a sublime looping finish over Alex Bass to give the Dons the lead — a goal worthy of winning any tie, let alone a play-off semi-final.

arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon beat Notts County to reach League Two play-off final
arts.sum: The Dons will face Walsall at Wembley on May 26 for a place in League One.

arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon see off Notts County to reach L2 play-off final
arts.sum: AFC Wimbledon beat Notts County 2-0 on aggregate to reach the League Two play-off final.

arts.ttl: Preview: AFC Wimbledon vs. Notts County - prediction, team news, lineups
arts.sum: Sports Mole previews Saturday's League Two clash between AFC Wimbledon and Notts County, including predictions, team news and possible lineups.

arts.ttl: Notts County boss Maynard expecting League Two play-off success against AFC Wimbledon
arts.sum: Notts County boss Stuart Maynard is backing his team to turn their League Two play-off semi-final deficit against AFC Wimbledon around and secure their spot at Wembley on Saturday. The Magpies face a Wimbledon side with the best defensive record in the league, while being without top scorer Alassana Jatta, who was sent off after a two-footed challenge on Alistair Smith in the dying minutes of the first leg.
